th them from a regulatory standpoint. 2) Toxicological science needs to be updated to determine the impact of the toxins in all kind of vectors (more and more are being discovered) and how they disseminate on the food chain. Also, the mode of action of many of this toxins is not understood or even known, and this affects also to the impact of the coexistence of several toxins in the same matrix. 3) Detection and regulation, as this requires the use of advance technology (mass spectrometry, biosensors, multitask screening etc) that is in many cases underdevelopped or not available, especially for many of the new toxins. Climate change, toxicology and detection affect so many areas of science that this book will try to keep the readers updated about the current state of the art.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aToxikologie. 4aUmwelttoxikologie. 4aUmweltwissenschaft. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Chemical & Biochemical.2bisacsh  aCyanotoxins.  aEnvironmental Science.  aEnvironmental Toxicology.  aMycotoxins.  aPhycotoxins.  aToxicology.1 aAguín, Olga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlfonso, Amparo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlfonso, Carmen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlvariño, Rebeca, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBotana, Ana M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBotana, Luis M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBotana, Luis M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCagide, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCao, Alejandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCost